    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-08-08T13:55:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-08-08T13:55:00-05:00" n="22"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                <head>22. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d22fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 320/8–858. Limited Official Use. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_NMH2">Newlin</persName>, cleared in substance by <persName
                            corresp="#p_NWT1">Nunley</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BRE3"
                            >Bacon</persName>, and approved by <persName corresp="#p_WWNJ1"
                            >Walmsley</persName> who signed for Dulles.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-08-08T14:55:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 8, 1958—2:55 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>133. Re: Hungary. Confirming Brown-Thacher telecon.<note n="2" xml:id="d22fn2">No
                        record of this telephone conversation has been found</note>
                </p>
                <p>In view unconfirmed reports certain <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss> dels may
                    raise Hungarian credentials issue initial plenary <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> should indicate to
                    friendly dels strong US hope matter not raised in plenary in order minimize
                    problems attendant Chinese representation. Should Hungarian credentials
                    nevertheless be raised in initial plenary, you should arrange for matter to be
                    considered first in Credentials Committee without prejudice ultimate
                    decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName>Dulles</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
